generate_moves.prompt:
You are agent_1. Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Your private information:
{agents->agent_1->private_information}
Your local goal:
{agents->agent_1->goal}
Produce an ordered list of primitive moves you will perform, each on its own line using the exact format 'agent_1: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'. Only include moves for disks A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H. Do not assume other agents' moves beyond what is necessary to ensure your moves are valid given the public initial state and rules.

You are agent_2. Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Your private information:
{agents->agent_2->private_information}
Your local goal:
{agents->agent_2->goal}
Produce an ordered list of primitive moves you will perform, each on its own line using the exact format 'agent_2: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'. Only include moves for disks I, J, K, L, M, N, O. Do not assume other agents' moves beyond what is necessary to ensure your moves are valid given the public initial state and rules.

